<title>ITALY: Italy's Genoa see July CPI at -0.1 pct mo/mo.</title>
<headline>Italy's Genoa see July CPI at -0.1 pct mo/mo.</headline>
<dateline>GENOA, Italy 1997-07-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Genoa said its July consumer price index (CPI) stood at -0.1 percent month-on-month and 0.8 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In June, Genoa's CPI inflation rate was 0.1 percent and 0.8 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Genoa is one of 11 Italian cities to publish inflation data on Monday and Tuesday. The city's CPI has a weighting of 2.88 percent on the national index. The 11 sample cities have a combined weighting of 75.66 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>The following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to June 1997):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		    -0.1   (0.1)     0.8   (0.8)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.1  (-0.4)	-   (-2.1)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0   (0.0)	-    (2.5)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.4   (0.0)	-    (4.3)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.0   (0.0)	-    (0.6)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0   (0.2)	-    (2.5)</p>
<p>    Transportation		   -0.1   (0.0)	-    (0.7)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.0   (0.1)	-    (0.0)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.0   (0.0)	-    (3.6)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.1   (0.7)	-    (1.1)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	-0.6   (0.3)	-   (-0.3)</p>
